            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "@justinmk Thank you for your reply. And BTW, thank you for your great work in supporting and developing NeoVim. It reminds me again, not to take this for granted and that I will again donate to the project to support your work!\n\nTrue, the VIM documentation states, that 'args' can be excluded. Because this does not work in NeoVim, because in NeoVim the session manager does not even recognize / know a sessionoption 'args'.\n\nAs long as the NeoVim documentation does not explicitly state that the sessionoption 'args' is not supported, I consider this to be a Bug and not an Enhancement, I hope you can agree on this.\n\nTrue, \"%argdel\" can help here, but this would be kind of a cumbersome workaround and not a solution to the problem.\n\nMy workaround is a bit more automated. I rarely use ':bd' directly, but rather via keymap. This allows to prepend the additional command \"%argdel\".\n\n```\nmap({ \"i\", \"v\", \"n\", \"s\" }, \"<a-q>\", function()\n  local listed_buffers = vim.fn.getbufinfo({ buflisted = 1 }) -- Get all listed buffers\n  if #listed_buffers == 1 then\n    vim.cmd(\"qa\") -- Exit Neovim if only one buffer is listed\n  else\n    vim.cmd(\"%argdel | bp | bd #\") -- Delete argument list, go to the previous buffer and delete the current one\n  end\nend, { desc = \"Quit buffer or exit Neovim if last buffer\" })\n```\n\nAn even more general workaround has been generated by Claude. \n```\n-- ~/.config/nvim/lua/plugins/persistent.lua:\n-- Clean up \"args\" to avoid session manager to save args as \"$argadd\" in the session file.\nreturn {\n  \"folke/persistence.nvim\",\n  opts = function(_, opts)\n    opts.options = { \"buffers\", \"curdir\", \"tabpages\", \"winsize\", \"help\", \"globals\", \"skiprtp\" }\n    return opts\n  end,\n  config = function(_, opts)\n    local persistence = require(\"persistence\")\n    persistence.setup(opts)\n\n    -- Patch save() to clear arglist and dead buffers before mksession\n    local original_save = persistence.save\n    persistence.save = function()\n      -- Clear argument list so no argadd lines are written\n      pcall(vim.cmd, \"argdelete *\")\n\n      -- Wipe buffers pointing to non-existent files\n      for _, buf in ipairs(vim.api.nvim_list_bufs()) do\n        if vim.api.nvim_buf_is_valid(buf) then\n          local bufname = vim.api.nvim_buf_get_name(buf)\n          if bufname ~= \"\" and vim.fn.filereadable(bufname) == 0 then\n            vim.api.nvim_buf_delete(buf, { force = true })\n          end\n        end\n      end\n\n      original_save()\n    end\n  end,\n}\n```\n",
